reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: El monitor es de muy buena calidad lo recomiendo para gaming 100%

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent for the money.
reviews.reviewText: I had a pretty specific featureset in mind (30-32", 2-4k, VA, non-curved, non-ultra-wide, high refresh rate, understated looks, FreeSync, brand that I know and trust) and this was one of a handful that fit the bill. Sale price was appealing, so I went with it.I'm pleased with it so far. There aren't a ton of settings, but the presets are pleasant out of the box, not much I'd change.If you know VA vs IPS, it's expected that viewing angles aren't quite as good as IPS, but still reasonable. Colors are rich for the price class, seem reasonably neutral. Contrast is improved over IPS. Don't expect OLED black levels, but they're quite decent on this. A subtle backlight sheam/haze is visible in darker scenes especially off-axis, but not as distracting as most IPS panels.Stand is great. Nice quality and excellent adjustability. Looks nice, too. There are reasonably tasteful "RGB" lights on the back panel, but I haven't yet figured out if you can disable them or change the color (default to blue). Either way, not terribly distracting or overly tacky.All in all, I really like it. Good image for the price, good build quality, understated looks (totally suitable for an office environment), affordable. Unless you're looking for pristine image accuracy/adjustability (for which you'll have to spend significantly more), this is a great option.

reviews.reviewText: This is the second one of this model that I’ve bought and they’re great. Picture is really good and smooth. Also for other comparable 1440p 32” monitors you would pay $50-100 more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great monitor for the (sale) price
reviews.reviewText: I was in the market for a white 1440p monitor that had a good refresh rate for a good price and this one delivered. I wouldn’t buy this at its full price because you can definitely find comparable models from other brands for less money. But at 250 it was a steal and I had to jump on it.Picture looks great and color is very accurate. White color goes well with the recent trend of white PC builds. The stand that is included with the monitor is really wide so it’d probably be best to make sure you have the space for it. My desk has a dedicated “ledge” where you’re supposed to put monitors but the stand was too wide to fit so I had to buy a dual monitor VESA mount for it and my older 1080p monitor.Took off one star due to the RGB strip on the back not working at all. Tried contacting Westinghouse support but they ultimately gave me the runaround and were less than helpful. The RGB strip not working isn’t really a dealbreaker for me but it’s annoying and frustrating that I can’t get a reply back from someone who knows what they’re talking about.Summary: Buy it if you can get it on sale like I did. At over 400 dollars for the regular price it’s simply not worth it.Update: I bought another monitor so that I would have dual matching 1440p screens. After installing the second monitor I was able to get the RGB on both monitors to function as intended.I am keeping the review at 4 stars because the customer support is basically nonexistent as other reviews have stated. The monitors themselves work great though and I’m very happy with the picture quality and performance. At their new price of 200 bucks it’s well worth it for how little you pay.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very impressed with this monitor
reviews.reviewText: This review is for the 'Flat Gaming 32" QHD VA 144Hz' monitor.When I saw the "Westinghouse" brand I thought this was going to be a budget product. If it is I don't know, but everything about it feels high quality. Things that called my attention right away where:+ The box was huge and the monitor came well packed and protected.+ The monitor's base is heavy and sturdy.+ It's very easy to adjust height, tilt and swivel.+ The included Display Port cable is thick and well insulated (with added ferrite ring cores).+ Beautiful matte VA display with no dead pixels and no light bleed on the corners and edges of the screen.+ Installation was very easy (you must supply your own Philips screwdriver).After a few minutes playing with the color settings, I was watching YouTube 4K demo videos and streaming movies on Netflix. My laptop can only do up to 120Hz and the frame rate increase was immediately apparent as soon as I enabled the feature.If the monitor didn't have the "Westinghouse" logo I would have thought it was an LG. I am happy with my purchase and would recommend this monitor.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Unclear Description and Awful Customer Support
reviews.reviewText: If I could give this product zero stars, I would. Nowhere in the product details are there any description on whether this monitor has an HDMI 2.0 or 1.0 connection. I combed over the manual and searched every place this information might be shared. I even called Westinghouse’s customer support to ask, and when I did, they asked for the model number, which I gave them. It’s right there on the box in big letters. I circled it in red in this photo. The customer support rep then kept telling me the model number didn’t exist, insisting I wasn’t giving her the right model number, which is why she can’t answer my question. I even offered to send her a photo to confirm I was reading the correct number. Then, she said she would email me so I can send her the photo but never did. However, what scares me the most is if I had any warranty issues, they’d most likely try not to honor it claiming my monitor model doesn’t exist. I will never buy a product from Westinghouse again and will definitely buy a higher end brand that makes all its specs clear from the beginning. Higher end brands will at least keep track of what models they actually sell and exist.

reviews.reviewTitle: Buena calidad y funcionamiento pero el instructivo deja que desear
reviews.reviewText: Excelente calidad aunque no viene con instrucciones claras de la configuración del monitor ya que dependiendo del modo de juego tienes que elegir los ajustes del visualización, el esamblaje fue fácil y también me gusta el funcionamiento de su brazo. Recomiendo checar las configuraciones de tu tarjeta de video para aprovechar el mayor rendimiento del monitor y utilizar un UPS para mejorar el ciclo de vida del mismo también.

Yo tengo una PS5 y cumplió muy bien, lo único malo es que no todos los juegos tienen 144hz, y eso además lo tienes que configurar manualmente para que lo juegos que tengan mayor calidad, por ejemplo, yo juego FIFA y warzone, fifa solo da para 60, pero warzone a 120, cuando lo cambias dentro del sistema de ps5, la calidad se cambia sola, solo que dentro del cod tienes que cambiar la calidad de imagen y listo.Todo muy bien la verdad, me gustó que se puede mover de arriba hacia abajo, ponerlo en vertical, recomendado el monitor 🫡
